[30;1m603 | [0m[35m        # just reverse, and we're good to go[0m

[30;1m4 | [0m[35mThe :class:`set` type brings the practical expressiveness of[0m
[30;1m5 | [0m[35mset theory to Python. It has a very rich API overall, but lacks a[0m
[30;1m6 | [0m[35mcouple of fundamental features. For one, sets are not ordered. On top[0m
[30;1m7 | [0m[35mof this, sets are not indexable, i.e, ``my_set[8]`` will raise an[0m
[30;1m8 | [0m[35m:exc:`TypeError`. The :class:`IndexedSet` type remedies both of these[0m
